               <head>Pereginus de Oppeln (?), <title>Sermones de sanctis</title>; Germany, 15th century, second quarter or middle</head>
               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <note>Fol. ii recto blank except for <q>Assumpta est maria in celum</q> and, added, <q>1459</q>; fol. ii verso blank.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="MS_Laud_Misc_70-item1">
                     <locus>(fols. 1r-114r)</locus>
                     <author key="person_63741243"><supplied>Peregrinus de Oppeln (?)</supplied></author>
                     <title key="work_3485">Sermones de sanctis (Hieron. de Salzburg collecti aut variati)</title>
                     <title key="work_16273">(Collectio sermonum ‘Flores de sanctis’ siue ‘Piper’)</title>
                     <rubric>Incipiunt sermones Iacobi de Voragino de Sanctis</rubric>
                     <rubric>De sancto Andrea Apostolo</rubric>
                     <incipit><quote>Simili pena servus cum Domino est afflictus.</quote> Sap. xviij. Filius Dei condolens humano generi vexillum sancte crucis in medio mundi consituit </incipit>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fols. 1ra-7rb)</locus>
                        <note>Schneyer IV, pp. 548–574, nos. 195–202.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fol. 7rb-8rb)</locus>
                        <rubric>Alius sermo de eodem <note>[St Thomas apostle]</note></rubric>
                        <incipit><quote>Affer manum tuam et mitte in latus meum</quote> Benigni homines habent modum dum vident aliquem ex caris amicis suis cecidisse</incipit>
                        <!--<note>Cf. Neustift/Novacella, Augustiner-Chorherrenstift, Cod. 78; also in Mainz, SB, Hs. I 191.</note>-->
                        <!-- https://manuscripta.at/hs_detail.php?ID=35415    -->
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fols. 8va-22rb)</locus>
                        <note>Schneyer, nos. 204–5, 111, 113, 206–219.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fols. 22rb-23ra)</locus>
                        <rubric>Item alius sermo de purificacione</rubric>
                        <incipit><cit>
                              <quote>Ecce ego mitto angelum meum <gap reason="editorial"/></quote>
                              <bibl>Mal. iijo</bibl>
                           </cit> In verbis istis iiijor notantur. Primum est quod dominus dicit Ecce ego mitto angelum meum. Secundum quod dicit</incipit>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fols. 23ra-34va)</locus>
                        <note>Schneyer, nos. 220–1, 124, 222–4, 126, 225, 127, 226–30, 232</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fol. 34va-b)</locus>
                        <rubric>Item sermo de eodem <note>[de Annunciatione]</note></rubric>
                        <incipit>Ita beata virgo fecit tria magna cum peccatoribus et precipue sibi seruentibus. </incipit>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fols. 34vb-54va)</locus>
                        <note>Schneyer, nos. 233, 129, 234–5, 131–2, 236–7, 134, 238–9, 136, 240–1, 137, 242, 140, 243–6.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fol. 54va-b)</locus>
                        <rubric>Alius sermo de eodem <note>[Johanne baptista]</note></rubric>
                        <incipit><cit>
                              <quote>Erit magnus coram domino etc.</quote>
                              <bibl>Luc. 1o</bibl>
                           </cit> Beatus Johannes magnus dicitur quia eius conceptio fuit miraculosa</incipit>
                        <!--<explicit>ad radicem est posita scilicet arboris. Expone. Rogemus.</explicit>-->
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fols. 54vb-97rb)</locus>
                        <note>Schneyer, nos. 247–9, 144–6, 250–9, 148, 260–1, 149, 262–4, 150–1, 265–76, 155, 277–8, 156, 279–85.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fol. 97rb-98rb)</locus>
                        <rubric>Sermo de angelis secundus</rubric>
                        <incipit><cit>
                              <quote>Omnes sunt administratorij spiritus</quote>
                              <bibl>Hebr. ijo</bibl>
                           </cit> Hodie agimus festum angelorum omnium et hoc propter plures causas</incipit>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fols. 98rb-107rb)</locus>
                        <note>Schneyer, nos. 286–99. </note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fol. 107rb-108rb)</locus>
                        <rubric>De animabus</rubric>
                        <incipit><cit>
                              <quote>Mittite partes eis qui non praeparauerunt sibi</quote>
                              <bibl>Esdre</bibl>
                           </cit> Conswetudo est in mundo quando aliquis usque ad mortem cruciatur mittit ad amicos suos dilectis</incipit>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fols. 108rb-va)</locus>
                        <rubric>De animabus</rubric>
                        <incipit><cit>
                              <quote>Miseremini mei etc.</quote>
                              <bibl>Iob</bibl>
                           </cit>
                           <unclear>Notandum</unclear> onere penitentie portando debemus fratres nostros iuuare exemplo Christi. Qui penam peccatorum portavit</incipit>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fols. 108va-109ra)</locus>
                        <note>Schneyer, no. 300.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fol. 109ra)</locus>
                        <rubric>De Martino</rubric>
                        <incipit>Nota septem dona dat deus anime sancte. Primum die martis dat sibi donum quod pascit eum</incipit>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fols. 109ra-114(b)ra; 114(b) verso blank)</locus>
                        <note>Schneyer, nos. 301, 174, 302–5, 185, 306–8.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <explicit><note>[De S. Katherina]</note> de triplici corona qua coronata est a domino nostro Ihesu Christo. Quere supra cui cum deo patre in unitate spiritus sancti viuit et regnat deus benedictus per infinita seculorum secula Amen.</explicit>
                     <finalRubric>Expliciunt sermones de sanctis Iacobi de Voragine. <note>[twice, once in red textualis]</note> Deo gratias.</finalRubric>
                     <note>Most of fol. 114b is cut away. The sermons are here attributed to <persName key="person_100198644">Jacobus de Voragine</persName>. The collection circulates as 'Piper' or 'Flores de sanctis' in other manuscripts, and Schneyer's attribution to Peregrinus de Oppeln has been doubted: <bibl>Günter Hägele, <title>Lateinische mittelalterliche Handschriften in Folio der Universitätsbibliothek Augsburg: Die Signaturengruppe Cod. I. 2. 2 und Cod. II. 1. 2 1–90</title> (Wiesbaden: Harrassowitz, 1996), p. 125</bibl> (Hs. II.1.2o.11). For the additional sermons here cf. for example the similar collections in the previously-cited Augsburg manuscript; <bibl subtype="external" type="ms">Neustift/Novacella, Augustiner-Chorherrenstift, Cod. 78</bibl>; <bibl subtype="external" type="ms">Innsbruck, Universitäts- und Landesbibliothek Tirol (ULBT), Cod. 71</bibl>; <bibl subtype="external" type="ms">BSB, Clm 3756</bibl>.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
